context: If the chef prepares the complete menu plan, then the head chef approves the menu. If the restaurant manager confirms the kitchen staff schedule, then the dinner service is officially set. Either the head chef does not approve the menu, or the dinner service is not officially set, or both. If the chef attends advanced culinary workshops, then the chef's cooking techniques improve. If the chef's cooking techniques improve, then the customer satisfaction ratings increase. Either the chef attends advanced culinary workshops, or the sous chef provides additional training, or both. If the sous chef provides additional training, then the chef receives specialized skill instruction. If the chef receives specialized skill instruction, then the dinner service is a success.
question: If the chef prepares the complete menu plan and the customer satisfaction ratings do not increase, is the dinner service a success?
true_response:
<lean>
axiom PrepareCompleteMenuPlan : Prop
axiom HeadChefApprovesMenu : Prop
axiom RestaurantManagerConfirmsKitchenStaffSchedule : Prop
axiom DinnerServiceOfficiallySet : Prop
axiom ChefAttendsAdvancedCulinaryWorkshops : Prop
axiom ChefCookingTechniquesImprove : Prop
axiom CustomerSatisfactionRatingsIncrease : Prop
axiom SousChefProvidesAdditionalTraining : Prop
axiom ChefReceivesSpecializedSkillInstruction : Prop
axiom DinnerServiceSuccess : Prop

axiom p1 : PrepareCompleteMenuPlan → HeadChefApprovesMenu
axiom p2 : RestaurantManagerConfirmsKitchenStaffSchedule → DinnerServiceOfficiallySet
axiom p3 : (¬ HeadChefApprovesMenu) ∨ (¬ DinnerServiceOfficiallySet)
axiom p4 : ChefAttendsAdvancedCulinaryWorkshops → ChefCookingTechniquesImprove
axiom p5 : ChefCookingTechniquesImprove → CustomerSatisfactionRatingsIncrease
axiom p6 : ChefAttendsAdvancedCulinaryWorkshops ∨ SousChefProvidesAdditionalTraining
axiom p7 : SousChefProvidesAdditionalTraining → ChefReceivesSpecializedSkillInstruction
axiom p8 : ChefReceivesSpecializedSkillInstruction → DinnerServiceSuccess

theorem goal :
  (PrepareCompleteMenuPlan ∧ ¬ CustomerSatisfactionRatingsIncrease) → DinnerServiceSuccess := by
  intro h
  have hNotInc : ¬ CustomerSatisfactionRatingsIncrease := And.right h
  cases p6 with
  | inl hAtt =>
      have hInc : CustomerSatisfactionRatingsIncrease := p5 (p4 hAtt)
      exact False.elim (hNotInc hInc)
  | inr hTrain =>
      exact p8 (p7 hTrain)
</lean>

context: If Max sets up a backup system for his files, then he secures his data against loss. If Max attends a cybersecurity workshop, then he learns about the latest security protocols. Max has made sure that he will either set up a backup system or attend the cybersecurity workshop, or both. If Max learns about the latest security protocols, then he updates his software accordingly. If he updates his software accordingly, then he strengthens his digital security. If Max subscribes to a tech magazine, then he keeps up with technology trends. He also ensures that either he learns about the latest security protocols or subscribes to a tech magazine, or both. If Max keeps up with technology trends, then he effectively manages his tech resources. If he effectively manages his tech resources, then his productivity increases.
question: If Max did not secure his data against loss and did not strengthen his digital security, did his productivity increase?
true_response:
<lean>
axiom Backup : Prop
axiom Secure : Prop
axiom Workshop : Prop
axiom Learn : Prop
axiom Update : Prop
axiom Strengthen : Prop
axiom Subscribe : Prop
axiom Trends : Prop
axiom Manage : Prop
axiom Productive : Prop

-- Premises
axiom p1 : Backup → Secure
axiom p2 : Workshop → Learn
axiom p3 : Backup ∨ Workshop
axiom p4 : Learn → Update
axiom p5 : Update → Strengthen
axiom p6 : Subscribe → Trends
axiom p7 : Learn ∨ Subscribe
axiom p8 : Trends → Manage
axiom p9 : Manage → Productive

-- Conclusion: If Max did not secure his data against loss and did not strengthen his digital security, then his productivity increases.
theorem goal : (¬Secure ∧ ¬Strengthen) → Productive := by
  intro h
  have hNotStrengthen : ¬Strengthen := h.right
  -- From ¬Strengthen and (Learn → Update) and (Update → Strengthen), derive ¬Learn
  have hNotLearn : ¬Learn := by
    intro hL
    have hU : Update := p4 hL
    have hS : Strengthen := p5 hU
    exact hNotStrengthen hS
  -- From (Learn ∨ Subscribe) and ¬Learn, deduce Subscribe
  have hSub : Subscribe := by
    cases p7 with
    | inl hL =>
      exact False.elim (hNotLearn hL)
    | inr hS =>
      exact hS
  -- Chain to Productive: Subscribe → Trends → Manage → Productive
  have hTr : Trends := p6 hSub
  have hMan : Manage := p8 hTr
  exact p9 hMan
</lean>
